Date: Wed, 19 Dec 2007 17:25:34
From: Angela Ralli [ralli@upatras.gr]
Subject: 1st Patras Conference of Graduate Students in Linguistics
E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=18-3820.html&submissionid=164468&topicid=3&msgnumber=1  

Full Title: 1st Patras Conference of Graduate Students in Linguistics 
Short Title: PICGSL 

Date: 28-Mar-2008 - 30-Mar-2008
Location: Patras, Greece 
Contact Person: Maria Pavlakou
Meeting Email: mpavlakou@upatras.gr

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 28-Mar-2008 

Meeting Description

The 1st Patras International Conference of Graduate Students in Linguistics will
be held at the University of Patras (March 28-30, 2008).
The aim of the conference is to bring graduate students together, from all over
the world. It addresses to graduate students (MA and PhD) in both Theoretical
and Applied Linguistics. The official languages of the conference are English
and Greek.
Information: www.philology.upatras.gr/PICGSL/home.htm (under construction) 

1st Patras International Conference of Graduate Students in Linguistics (PICGL)
Patras, Greece, March 28-30, 2008

2nd Call for Papers
Deadline extended

The postgraduate students in Linguistics of the University of Patras are
organising the first Patras International Conference of Graduate students in
Linguistics (28th-30th March, 2008). The conference addresses to graduate
students (MA or PhD) from all over the world who wish to present original
research in any field of linguistics (phonetics, phonology, morphology, syntax,
semantics, pragmatics, historical linguistics, discourse analysis,
sociolinguistics, psycholinguistics, computational linguistics, lexicology,
lexicography, language acquisition, language teaching, etc.).  

Invited Speakers
Alexandra Georgakopoulou, King's College London
Brian Joseph, The Ohio State University
Eva Kehayia, McGill University
Io Manolessou, University of Patras
Dimitris Papazachariou, University of Patras
Sergio Scalise, University of Bologna
Neil Smith, Emer. Prof. University College London

Deadline for abstract submission extended 
Send an abstract (150-200 words, Word or Pdf file) electronically at
picgl@upatras.gr until the 20th of January 2008. 

Information
For information, please visit the site of the Department of Philology, under
Conferences: www.philology.upatras.gr



	
